<TITLE> Owen to miss Newcastle's derby game with Sunderland </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, Oct 24 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Michael Owen will miss Newcastle United's away match against north east rivals Sunderland on Saturday because of a groin strain, the Premier League club said. The England striker is also likely to miss Newcastle's next game at home to West Bromwich Albion. "Michael, unfortunately, will not be fit in time for Sunderland and, of course, that's a blow to lose a striker of his calibre," stand-in manager Joe Kinnear told the club's website (www.nufc.premiumtv.co.uk). Meanwhile, Newcastle defender Habib Beye has had the red card he received against Manchester City on Monday overturned and can play at Sunderland, the club said. Beye was shown the red card after a last-ditch tackle on City's Brazilian striker Robinho which resulted in a penalty. Television replays showed that Beye made contact with the ball before Robinho tumbled over his outstretched leg
